                </script></div></div></div></div><div id="content" class="_content_16y43_1" data-component="annotation" data-testid="annotation_testID"><p class="p1"><span class="s1">Searching for schools in Hong Kong can be a daunting task. How does play centred learning work? What should you consider when looking at bilingual education? And how exactly should you be doing applications? We chat to four leading educational experts about how to choose the right school for your child.&nbsp;</span></p></div></div><div class="_landerNewsletter_5hv1r_10 _hidden_5hv1r_20"><div class="_container_sxeje_1 newsletter_lander" data-component="inline-newsletter" data-newsletter-type="lander" data-testid="inline-newsletter_testID"><div class="row"><div class="panel_form"><div class="_section_heading_sxeje_6"><p class="_form_title_sxeje_30">An email you’ll actually love</p><label class="_label_sxeje_39">Get into a relationship with our newsletter. Discover the best of the city, first.</label></div><form class="_section_form_sxeje_10"><div class="_loading_overlay_sxeje_46 loading_overlay"></div><div class="_zone_input_sxeje_18"><label class="_text-hide_v9moj_1" for="lander-newsletter-email">Enter email address</label><input type="email" id="lander-newsletter-email" class="_email_sxeje_77" placeholder="Enter email address" required=""/><img class="_loading_icon_sxeje_56 loading_icon" src="data:image/gif;base64," alt="Loading animation"/><div class="_error_sxeje_63 error">Déjà vu! We already have this email. Try another?</div></div><div class="_zone_submit_sxeje_24"><input type="submit" class="_submit_sxeje_87" value="Subscribe"/></div></form><div class="section_consent"><p class="_consent_sxeje_110">By entering your email address you agree to our <a href="https://www.timeout.com/terms-of-use" target="_blank">Terms of Use</a> and <a href="https://www.timeout.com/privacy-notice" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a> and consent to receive emails from Time Out about news, events, offers and partner promotions.</p></div></div><div class="_panel_success_sxeje_120 panel_success"><p class="_success_title_sxeje_124">🙌 Awesome, you&#x27;re subscribed!</p><p class="_success_thanks_sxeje_131">Thanks for subscribing! Look out for your first newsletter in your inbox soon!</p></div></div></div></div><div data-zone-name="small_list" class="zone _zoneFirst_abr0c_5 _zone_abr0c_1" data-track-view="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;zone_1::small_list:1_tiles&quot;,&quot;events&quot;:[&quot;event233&quot;]}" data-component="lazy-load-zone" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251045&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251045?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}" data-testid="zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_zoneTitle_4w5ul_29"></div><div class="_zoneItems_4w5ul_1 zoneItems"><article class="tile _article_tpquo_1" data-testid="tile-zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_imageContainer_tpquo_62"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><div class="_imageWrap_tpquo_242"><img src="https://media.timeout.com/images/103556778/750/562/image.jpg" srcSet="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" data-srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/103556778/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556778/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556778/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556778/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w" data-sizes="auto" class="lazyload _image_tpquo_62 aspect-ratio-4-3" title="Thomas Ho – Programme director of early learning centre, KinderU" alt="Thomas Ho – Programme director of early learning centre, KinderU" width="750" height="562" data-testid="responsive-image_testID"/></div></div></div><div class="articleContent _articleContent_tpquo_229"><div class="_title_tpquo_9"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><h3 class="_h3_cuogz_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Thomas Ho – Programme director of early learning centre, KinderU</h3></div></div><div class="_summaryContainer_tpquo_43"><input type="checkbox" class="showMoreCheckbox _checkbox_lde2r_21" id="show-more-1-0-1" data-animated-chevron-input="true" role="button"/><label for="show-more-1-0-1" class="showMoreLabel _label_lde2r_1" data-trans-show="Show more" data-trans-hide="Show less" data-component="show-more"><span class="_animatedChevron_c3wq1_1 _medium_c3wq1_29"></span></label><div class="summaryCollapsed _summary_tpquo_21"><p class="_p_1vat8_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p class="p1"><strong><span class="s1">Most kindergartens go for a play centred approach. Do you think that this is the best way to teach young children?<br /> </span></strong>Absolutely. When it comes to children they aren&rsquo;t aware of whether something is difficult or not. So, if something is difficult but fun they&rsquo;ll stick at it. But if something is easy but boring they won&rsquo;t do it. Right brain education is therefore very important. When you&rsquo;re using the right side of the brain you&rsquo;re relaxed and having fun, so you&rsquo;ll remember things much more quickly.</p>
<p class="p3"><strong>How long should a child of kindergarten age be spending at school?<br /> </strong><span class="s1">Well I think how long a child spends in school each day depends on what he or she has after school, as well as on the quality of the school. If a school has the facilities to offer extra activities, such as Kung Fu or choir practice, it&rsquo;s best for the child to stay in school for a full day. Otherwise, if you send a child to a half day school they&rsquo;ll be running all over Hong Kong for extra curricular activities afterwards anyway. It&rsquo;s best to just keep them under one roof. The child needs to bond with the premises and the people. The thing is, that in Hong Kong most parents work full days, so children are then left with their helpers at home and despite helpers being absolutely marvelous people, they&rsquo;re not teachers, so keeping the child with the helper all day doesn&rsquo;t always help. But it&rsquo;s very dependent on the family situation.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong>What should parents be asking when looking for schools for their child?<br /> </strong>Number one for a teacher would be &lsquo;How long have you been in the industry and why did you choose to become a teacher?&rsquo; The motive is very important, you need to get a sense of their passion. You also need to understand what the school&rsquo;s vision and mission is and then ask people in the school about it. This should come easily if they have a clear understanding of the school&rsquo;s vision and are taking it seriously.<br /> <br /> <strong><span class="s3">KinderU </span></strong><span class="s4"><em><a href="http://www.kinderu.org" target="_blank">kinderu.org</a>.</em></span></p></p></div></div></div></article></div><div class="_viewMoreCta_4w5ul_10" data-component="infinite-scroll" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251045&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251045?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}"><a class="_a_12eii_1" data-track-click="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;click on read more button&quot;,&quot;prop59&quot;:&quot;small_list::read more button&quot;}" target="_self" rel="" data-data-layer="{&quot;triggerOn&quot;:0,&quot;payload&quot;:{&quot;action&quot;:&quot;link - external&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:&quot;GP Engagement&quot;,&quot;label&quot;:&quot;read more button&quot;}}" data-testID="view-more-cta_testID"><span class="_textContent_12eii_36">Show more</span><img class="_loadingIcon_1uzy0_1" src="data:image/gif;base64," alt="Loading animation"/></a></div></div><div data-zone-name="small_list" class="zone _zone_abr0c_1" data-track-view="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;zone_2::small_list:1_tiles&quot;,&quot;events&quot;:[&quot;event233&quot;]}" data-component="lazy-load-zone" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251046&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251046?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}" data-testid="zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_zoneTitle_4w5ul_29"></div><div class="_zoneItems_4w5ul_1 zoneItems"><article class="tile _article_tpquo_1" data-testid="tile-zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_imageContainer_tpquo_62"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><div class="_imageWrap_tpquo_242"><img src="https://media.timeout.com/images/103556780/750/562/image.jpg" srcSet="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" data-srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/103556780/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556780/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556780/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556780/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w" data-sizes="auto" class="lazyload _image_tpquo_62 aspect-ratio-4-3" title="Ruth Benny – Founder of admission consultants, Top Schools" alt="Ruth Benny – Founder of admission consultants, Top Schools" width="750" height="562" data-testid="responsive-image_testID"/></div></div></div><div class="articleContent _articleContent_tpquo_229"><div class="_title_tpquo_9"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><h3 class="_h3_cuogz_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Ruth Benny – Founder of admission consultants, Top Schools</h3></div></div><div class="_summaryContainer_tpquo_43"><input type="checkbox" class="showMoreCheckbox _checkbox_lde2r_21" id="show-more-2-0-1" data-animated-chevron-input="true" role="button"/><label for="show-more-2-0-1" class="showMoreLabel _label_lde2r_1" data-trans-show="Show more" data-trans-hide="Show less" data-component="show-more"><span class="_animatedChevron_c3wq1_1 _medium_c3wq1_29"></span></label><div class="summaryCollapsed _summary_tpquo_21"><p class="_p_1vat8_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p class="p1"><strong>What made you decide to set up Top Schools?<br /> </strong><span class="s2">I guess I just saw an opportunity. There&rsquo;s nothing quite like what we do. We serve a real purpose in the community. The system is really complex, so often parents need help being guided through the process. If you&rsquo;re looking to choose a private school here in Hong Kong, there&rsquo;s just so much choice and there&rsquo;s so much money that&rsquo;s misspent.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s3"><strong>How is money misspent?<br /> </strong></span><span class="s2">We just did a little analysis and figured out that the average parent spends about $21,000 on applications for just one child. We would never advocate that a parent should spend that much on applications. So a very simple tweak to the whole process, which is something that we would do for our clients, is to create focused applications. You don&rsquo;t need to do six - that&rsquo;s almost always too many - we&rsquo;d recommend three to four max. <br /> <br /> </span><span class="s3"><strong>Do all schools require application fees?</strong><br /> </span><span class="s2">Yes. Pre schools charge anything between $40 and $8,000. But normally the bigger international private schools charge $1,000 upwards. So, the one thing I&rsquo;d like to change about this system is the amount of misspent money. Of course there'll be times that you absolutely have to pay this, but only when you&rsquo;ve done the thorough research and understand that it&rsquo;s worth spending. But most of the applications are just random &ndash; there&rsquo;s not much thought going into them.</span></p>
<p class="p2"><strong>Bilingual education is becoming more popular, how do you advise parents looking at this route for their children?</strong><br /> <span class="s2">This is an area close to my heart. We have so many parents who come to us who want &lsquo;strong Mandarin&rsquo;, but what does &lsquo;strong&rsquo; mean? You&rsquo;ve got to first define that because it&rsquo;s a relative, elastic term.</span></p>
<p class="p2"><span class="s2"><strong>Also, to what extent are you as parents willing to support your child learning Mandarin? </strong><br /> It&rsquo;s a lifestyle choice, not just a school choice. You can&rsquo;t just dump your kids in that school and say, &lsquo;Okay, well the school&rsquo;s going to take care of this, my child&rsquo;s going to learn Chinese,&rsquo; especially when you don&rsquo;t have the support at home. It&rsquo;s difficult. In the younger years you just have to suck it up and get tutors. You just really have to make sacrifices.<br /> <br /> </span><span class="s2"><strong>Top Schools&nbsp;</strong></span><span class="s2"><em><a href="#" target="_blank">topschools.com.hk</a>.</em></span></p></p></div></div></div></article></div><div class="_viewMoreCta_4w5ul_10" data-component="infinite-scroll" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251046&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251046?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}"><a class="_a_12eii_1" data-track-click="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;click on read more button&quot;,&quot;prop59&quot;:&quot;small_list::read more button&quot;}" target="_self" rel="" data-data-layer="{&quot;triggerOn&quot;:0,&quot;payload&quot;:{&quot;action&quot;:&quot;link - external&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:&quot;GP Engagement&quot;,&quot;label&quot;:&quot;read more button&quot;}}" data-testID="view-more-cta_testID"><span class="_textContent_12eii_36">Show more</span><img class="_loadingIcon_1uzy0_1" src="data:image/gif;base64," alt="Loading animation"/></a></div></div><div data-zone-name="small_list" class="zone _zone_abr0c_1" data-track-view="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;zone_3::small_list:1_tiles&quot;,&quot;events&quot;:[&quot;event233&quot;]}" data-component="lazy-load-zone" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251047&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251047?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}" data-testid="zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_zoneTitle_4w5ul_29"></div><div class="_zoneItems_4w5ul_1 zoneItems"><article class="tile _article_tpquo_1" data-testid="tile-zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_imageContainer_tpquo_62"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><div class="_imageWrap_tpquo_242"><img src="https://media.timeout.com/images/103556781/750/562/image.jpg" srcSet="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" data-srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/103556781/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556781/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556781/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103556781/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w" data-sizes="auto" class="lazyload _image_tpquo_62 aspect-ratio-4-3" title="Belinda Greer – CEO of the English Schools Foundation" alt="Belinda Greer – CEO of the English Schools Foundation" width="750" height="562" data-testid="responsive-image_testID"/></div><figcaption class="_figcaption_1ctb8_1" data-testid="image-credits_testID"><span>Photo by Chris Tsang</span></figcaption></div></div><div class="articleContent _articleContent_tpquo_229"><div class="_title_tpquo_9"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><h3 class="_h3_cuogz_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Belinda Greer – CEO of the English Schools Foundation</h3></div></div><div class="_summaryContainer_tpquo_43"><input type="checkbox" class="showMoreCheckbox _checkbox_lde2r_21" id="show-more-3-0-1" data-animated-chevron-input="true" role="button"/><label for="show-more-3-0-1" class="showMoreLabel _label_lde2r_1" data-trans-show="Show more" data-trans-hide="Show less" data-component="show-more"><span class="_animatedChevron_c3wq1_1 _medium_c3wq1_29"></span></label><div class="summaryCollapsed _summary_tpquo_21"><p class="_p_1vat8_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p class="p1"><span class="s1"><strong>What&rsquo;s the best way for parents to get a feel for a school that they may be considering for their child?<br /> </strong></span>I think it&rsquo;s really important for parents to visit the schools and to go into classes as well as receiving a tour. In addition to having a range of questions to ask, I think they should be looking themselves to see evidence of the school&rsquo;s values and the school&rsquo;s mission. They should be looking at what&rsquo;s happening in the classroom. Are children actively engaged? Are they enjoying learning? Then I think they need to ask the school about how <span class="s1">they organise the learning and how they meet children&rsquo;s learning needs and interests. Obviously the parents would be interested in the school in terms of performance, so they&rsquo;d need to look at what school values in terms of students&rsquo; achievement. Are they just looking at academic results, or are they looking at standards that the school achieves in a broader context? For my children I&rsquo;d certainly look for a school that not only has high academic standards, but also offers a range of opportunities for wider achievements.</span></p>
<p class="p4"><strong>With kids who have very different interests, do you think it&rsquo;s good to separate them?<br /> </strong>I think a really affective school meets the needs of all students. If parents find a really effective school then the school should cater for the differences in families. The only time I think that a family would be right to consider different schools is when a child may have complex learning needs. But I think for siblings and families to feel connected and part of the community there are advantages to childrn attending the same school.&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p4"><strong>A lot of kids in HK transition between schools. How do you think they&rsquo;re best supported in this process?&nbsp;<br /> </strong>I think it can sometimes be overplayed. I think most students moving from primary to secondary look forward to a change and often go with friends. I think it is maybe different for students who move into Hong Kong, particularly if they&rsquo;re a bit older and they&rsquo;re leaving their friends and all that they know in their home country. It all comes down to having really good communication from the school that the child is leaving to the school that the child is moving to, to try and make it as seamless as possible. <br /> <br /> <span class="s3">ESF</span> <span class="s4"><em><a href="http://www.esf.edu.hk" target="_blank">esf.edu.hk</a>.</em></span></p></p></div></div></div></article></div><div class="_viewMoreCta_4w5ul_10" data-component="infinite-scroll" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251047&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251047?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}"><a class="_a_12eii_1" data-track-click="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;click on read more button&quot;,&quot;prop59&quot;:&quot;small_list::read more button&quot;}" target="_self" rel="" data-data-layer="{&quot;triggerOn&quot;:0,&quot;payload&quot;:{&quot;action&quot;:&quot;link - external&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:&quot;GP Engagement&quot;,&quot;label&quot;:&quot;read more button&quot;}}" data-testID="view-more-cta_testID"><span class="_textContent_12eii_36">Show more</span><img class="_loadingIcon_1uzy0_1" src="data:image/gif;base64," alt="Loading animation"/></a></div></div><div data-zone-name="small_list" class="zone _zone_abr0c_1" data-track-view="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;zone_4::small_list:1_tiles&quot;,&quot;events&quot;:[&quot;event233&quot;]}" data-component="lazy-load-zone" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251048&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251048?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}" data-testid="zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_zoneTitle_4w5ul_29"></div><div class="_zoneItems_4w5ul_1 zoneItems"><article class="tile _article_tpquo_1" data-testid="tile-zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_imageContainer_tpquo_62"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><div class="_imageWrap_tpquo_242"><img src="https://media.timeout.com/images/103557151/750/562/image.jpg" srcSet="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" data-srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/103557151/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103557151/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103557151/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103557151/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w" data-sizes="auto" class="lazyload _image_tpquo_62 aspect-ratio-4-3" title="Dr Maggie Koong – Chief Principal of Victoria Education Organisation " alt="Dr Maggie Koong – Chief Principal of Victoria Education Organisation " width="750" height="562" data-testid="responsive-image_testID"/></div></div></div><div class="articleContent _articleContent_tpquo_229"><div class="_title_tpquo_9"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><h3 class="_h3_cuogz_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">Dr Maggie Koong – Chief Principal of Victoria Education Organisation </h3></div></div><div class="_summaryContainer_tpquo_43"><input type="checkbox" class="showMoreCheckbox _checkbox_lde2r_21" id="show-more-4-0-1" data-animated-chevron-input="true" role="button"/><label for="show-more-4-0-1" class="showMoreLabel _label_lde2r_1" data-trans-show="Show more" data-trans-hide="Show less" data-component="show-more"><span class="_animatedChevron_c3wq1_1 _medium_c3wq1_29"></span></label><div class="summaryCollapsed _summary_tpquo_21"><p class="_p_1vat8_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p class="p1"><strong><span class="s3">How has early years education changed since you started?<br /> </span></strong>Education is like a pendulum. A lot of the time it swings from the traditional to all of a sudden being very progressive &ndash; currently I think it&rsquo;s leaning to a more traditional approach. Additionally, kindergarten is being talked about a lot more, parents want their children to have as much of a head start as possible. Parents seem to be planning right from the word go, sometimes even before the mother&rsquo;s pregnant! &nbsp;Whereas, in the past, they would look at options when kids were one or two years old.&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p3"><span class="s3"><strong>Early years education is very centred around play. How is this structured?<br /> </strong></span><span class="s3">Play is part of children&rsquo;s language, so it&rsquo;s a great way of communicating with them. Take flashcards, for example. If you just go through them, they&rsquo;ll get bored, but if you put them on the table and get them to match them &ndash; make it a game &ndash; they&rsquo;re more motivated.</span></p>
<p class="p4"><span class="s3">There are four types of play that we use to engage the children. Firstly, we have free play, where kids can run around and do what they want. Then we have guided play, where they&rsquo;re encouraged to take part in different activities, like setting up a tea party, which would relate to a book they may have been reading. Then there&rsquo;s discovery play, where they may be experimenting with light and shadow or something else. Then finally there&rsquo;s intentional play, which has an objective. You want children to learn something through what they&rsquo;re playing.</span></p>
<p class="p3"><strong><span class="s3">What key things should parents ask and look for when selecting a kindergarten for their child?</span></strong><br /> <span class="s3">Structural things like teacher to student ratio, of course. But other important questions that parents often omit to ask are things like, &lsquo;What sort of role do you expect parents to play?&rsquo; and &lsquo;What sort of professional development do you provide for your teachers?&rsquo; This is really important. It shows the progression of the school and the development of the staff. Parents may also have something in mind for their child&rsquo;s education, so asking about the philosophy really helps them to understand if they&rsquo;re getting the right sort of environment &ndash; it&rsquo;s like a matchmaking service in that way! <br /> <br /> <strong>Victoria Education Organisation&nbsp;</strong></span><span class="s3"><em><a href="http://www.victoria.edu.hk" target="_blank">victoria.edu.hk</a>.</em></span></p></p></div></div></div></article></div><div class="_viewMoreCta_4w5ul_10" data-component="infinite-scroll" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251048&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251048?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}"><a class="_a_12eii_1" data-track-click="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;click on read more button&quot;,&quot;prop59&quot;:&quot;small_list::read more button&quot;}" target="_self" rel="" data-data-layer="{&quot;triggerOn&quot;:0,&quot;payload&quot;:{&quot;action&quot;:&quot;link - external&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:&quot;GP Engagement&quot;,&quot;label&quot;:&quot;read more button&quot;}}" data-testID="view-more-cta_testID"><span class="_textContent_12eii_36">Show more</span><img class="_loadingIcon_1uzy0_1" src="data:image/gif;base64," alt="Loading animation"/></a></div></div><div data-zone-name="small_list" class="zone _zone_abr0c_1" data-track-view="{&quot;pev2&quot;:&quot;zone_5::small_list:3_tiles&quot;,&quot;events&quot;:[&quot;event233&quot;]}" data-component="lazy-load-zone" data-params="{&quot;zoneId&quot;:&quot;1251049&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/601/en-GB/pages/94969/zone/1251049?site_id=hk-hongkong&amp;pageNumber=:pageNumber&amp;pageSize=10&amp;gp-web=true&quot;}" data-testid="zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_zoneTitle_4w5ul_29"><h2 class="_h2_1ikgb_1" data-testid="zone-title_testID"><span>New school openings in Hong Kong</span></h2></div><div class="_zoneItems_4w5ul_1 zoneItems"><article class="tile _article_tpquo_1" data-testid="tile-zone-small-list_testID"><div class="_imageContainer_tpquo_62"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><div class="_imageWrap_tpquo_242"><img src="https://media.timeout.com/images/103559032/750/562/image.jpg" srcSet="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" data-srcset="https://media.timeout.com/images/103559032/380/285/image.jpg 380w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103559032/750/562/image.jpg 750w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103559032/1024/768/image.jpg 1024w,https://media.timeout.com/images/103559032/1372/1029/image.jpg 1372w" data-sizes="auto" class="lazyload _image_tpquo_62 aspect-ratio-4-3" title="American School Hong Kong" alt="American School Hong Kong" width="750" height="562" data-testid="responsive-image_testID"/></div></div></div><div class="articleContent _articleContent_tpquo_229"><div class="_title_tpquo_9"><div data-testid="tile-link_testID"><h3 class="_h3_cuogz_1" data-testid="tile-title_testID">American School Hong Kong</h3></div></div><div class="_summaryContainer_tpquo_43"><input type="checkbox" class="showMoreCheckbox _checkbox_lde2r_21" id="show-more-5-0-1" data-animated-chevron-input="true" role="button"/><label for="show-more-5-0-1" class="showMoreLabel _label_lde2r_1" data-trans-show="Show more" data-trans-hide="Show less" data-component="show-more"><span class="_animatedChevron_c3wq1_1 _medium_c3wq1_29"></span></label><div class="summaryCollapsed _summary_tpquo_21"><p class="_p_1vat8_1" data-testid="summary_testID"><p class="p1">This August the American School Hong Kong (ASHK) opened its doors in Tai Po. The school teaches both the US common core and IB Diploma programme to kindergarten aged through to grade six aged children. The middle school and high school are scheduled to open in 2017 and 2018 respectively. &nbsp;</p>
<p class="p3"><em>6 Ma Chung Rd, Tai Po, New Territories, 3919 4111; <a href="http://www.ashk.edu.hk" target="_blank">ashk.edu.hk</a></em></p>
